        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1259",
        "content": "Houses have their own ways of dying, falling as variously as the generations of men, some with a tragic roar, some quietly, but to an after life in the city of ghosts, while from others-and thus was the death of Wickham Place-the spirit slips before the body perishes.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-low_s-normal_e-low",
